00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,252
I'm serious!

274
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:21,496
You have a big heart.

275
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:29,613
April!

276
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:31,612
Look who's here!

277
00:25:32,460 --> 00:25:35,452
I wanna take it with you,
it'll make us happy.

278
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,656
I'm already happy with you.

279
00:25:39,020 --> 00:25:40,851
Not this happy.

280
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:18,573
Let's go!

281
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:22,576
Hold on, be right there.

282
00:26:27,780 --> 00:26:28,929
Howdy.

283
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:31,216
Window's open, what's going on?

284
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:33,018
Where's the cowboy?

285
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:36,218
What are you doing John Wayne?
C'mon!

286
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:39,015
We should love people, not cars.

287
00:26:39,460 --> 00:26:40,654
I'm serious!

288
00:26:41,020 --> 00:26:42,578
What'll we do?

289
00:26:42,820 --> 00:26:46,130
We don't belong to all this,
you're all trapped inside.

290
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:48,814
We're just trying to go somewhere.

291
00:26:49,060 --> 00:26:50,459
Look!

292
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:53,055
- Everyone out!
- The hell with cars!

293
00:26:53,300 --> 00:26:55,655
- Hug me!
- No, you do it.

294
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:59,653
- Preach it, Texan!
- Yeah, I'll preach!

295
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:02,016
Preach it, brother.

296
00:27:02,260 --> 00:27:03,932
See, I'm preaching!

297
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:05,738
- Quit it.
- What?

298
00:27:05,980 --> 00:27:09,256
- Are you nuts?
- No, I'm the sanest of all.

299
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:11,855
- Yeah, right.
- It's true, look.

300
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:14,455
They're sitting
in their boxes driving.

301
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:19,858
Look how many boxes,
an endless line!

302
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:39,810
When'll the effect wear off?

303
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:42,971
In a while.

304
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:45,256
You'll be fine tomorrow.

305
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:49,332
What's on your mind?

306
00:27:49,780 --> 00:27:51,293
Dunno,

307
00:27:51,540 --> 00:27:54,293
there are lots of things
I'd like to do, but...

308
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:56,616
I'll never be able to.

309
00:27:57,460 --> 00:27:59,610
You can do anything you want.

310
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:05,494
You can even become
anything you want, if you just...

311
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:07,692
Decide and...

312
00:28:08,340 --> 00:28:09,614
do it.

313
00:28:09,860 --> 00:28:12,693
It's like waiting
for life to start over.

314
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:17,134
A new start, understand?

315
00:28:17,460 --> 00:28:20,975
At times I'd like
to step outside of my heart.

316
00:28:22,740 --> 00:28:25,698
Take a walk under a starry sky.

317
00:28:27,260 --> 00:28:30,218
And listen to nothing but the wind.

318
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:33,691
I'd like to talk
and hear my real voice.

319
00:28:33,940 --> 00:28:37,694
- Do you talk with your real voice?
- Dunno.

320
00:28:40,140 --> 00:28:41,653
What is it?

321
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:46,052
When you don't hear any other voices
in your head while talking.

322
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:49,530
You can say what you really want,

323
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:53,538
you don't say things
you're not interested in.

324
00:28:54,220 --> 00:28:56,973
Are you sincere with yourself?

325
00:28:59,220 --> 00:29:00,972
Not always.

326
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:05,376
But I am now.

327
00:29:09,220 --> 00:29:10,778
Me too.

328
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:20,733
- Hi.
- Where the hell have you been?

329
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:23,057
I slept at April's.

330
00:29:23,580 --> 00:29:25,536
Hold on, dammit!

331
00:29:29,820 --> 00:29:31,378
Were you with him?

332
00:29:34,260 --> 00:29:37,013
I was up all night
worried sick about you.

333
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:40,411
- Your girlfriend didn't comfort you?
- Come here!

334
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:43,413
- I'm not done talking.
- Leave me alone.

335
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:45,173
Come out!

336
00:29:45,420 --> 00:29:47,934
- Open the door.
- No way!

337
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:49,977
Open the damn door.

338
00:29:52,220 --> 00:29:56,179
We'll discuss this tonight,
make sure you're here when I get back.

339
00:29:56,420 --> 00:29:58,092
- Hear me?
- Yes.

340
00:29:58,340 --> 00:30:00,296
- What?
- Yes!

341
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:13,933
You have something of mine,
I won't give up easily!

342
00:30:14,180 --> 00:30:16,740
If I come in, I'll open fire!

343
00:30:25,860 --> 00:30:27,816
You got some nerve shooting me.

344
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:31,420
Half that stuff's mine,
there's plenty for all!

345
00:30:31,660 --> 00:30:33,571
Knock it off!

346
00:30:34,260 --> 00:30:36,410
Leave me alone, idiot!

347
00:30:37,060 --> 00:30:39,415
Mind your business
if you don't want trouble.

348
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:41,810
You have some screws loose!

349
00:30:44,060 --> 00:30:46,016
Your greed will be your death,

350
00:30:46,260 --> 00:30:47,773
'cause you...

351
00:30:49,420 --> 00:30:50,773
You are greedy

352
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:54,569
and you'll squeal like a pig
when I come in that door!

353
00:30:55,460 --> 00:30:56,813
Fuck.

354
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:08,818
All this for a few gold nuggets.

355
00:31:14,820 --> 00:31:17,778
I bet this is part of human madness.

356
00:31:34,780 --> 00:31:36,498
Almost there.

357
00:31:39,020 --> 00:31:41,580
- Is that them?
- Sure is.

358
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:44,058
Like 'em?

359
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:46,733
Good.

360
00:31:47,020 --> 00:31:48,578
Pick one.

361
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,899
Hey there.

362
00:31:54,140 --> 00:31:55,732
Easy...

363
00:31:56,380 --> 00:31:57,733
Good boy.

364
00:32:02,460 --> 00:32:04,018
Let's go.

365
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:34,892
What do you think?

366
00:32:36,020 --> 00:32:37,612
It's beautiful.

367
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:39,931
Yeah, it sure is.

368
00:33:05,180 --> 00:33:07,535
Do you think things have meaning?

369
00:33:08,660 --> 00:33:10,218
Huh?

370
00:33:12,220 --> 00:33:16,054
Do you think everything's destiny
is already...

371
00:33:16,860 --> 00:33:18,612
written?

372
00:33:19,260 --> 00:33:21,216
That's an interesting thought.

373
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:23,218
I came here often.

374
00:33:23,540 --> 00:33:25,496
I looked at that branch and

375
00:33:26,020 --> 00:33:28,056
asked myself if it had a purpose.

376
00:33:29,780 --> 00:33:31,452
Maybe it's here...

377
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,496
to create shade.

378
00:33:35,220 --> 00:33:36,858
Or maybe...

379
00:33:37,100 --> 00:33:40,649
it'll get cut to make furniture
for somebody's home.

380
00:33:42,380 --> 00:33:44,416
Maybe it's just here for the swing.

381
00:33:47,460 --> 00:33:51,612
Maybe it's just here
to balance the entire tree.

382
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:55,170
I'd opt for the swing idea.

383
00:33:55,420 --> 00:33:57,376
It seems like a good idea.

384
00:34:00,260 --> 00:34:03,252
And seeing you on it,
I know I'm right.

385
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:39,936
Can I watch?

386
00:34:42,700 --> 00:34:43,974
Sure.

387
00:34:49,340 --> 00:34:51,171
Where's your sister?

388
00:34:51,420 --> 00:34:52,978
Dunno.

389
00:34:53,980 --> 00:34:56,335
Are you still mad at her?

390
00:34:57,980 --> 00:35:00,335
I love your sister, it's just that...

391
00:35:01,380 --> 00:35:04,736
at times
she makes me lose my patience.

392
00:35:06,380 --> 00:35:08,052
What do you like about her?

393
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:10,052
She's got moxie.

394
00:35:10,420 --> 00:35:12,172
What's that?

395
00:35:12,460 --> 00:35:13,813
It means...

396
00:35:15,020 --> 00:35:18,376
she's got guts,
she's not submissive.

397
00:35:20,460 --> 00:35:23,418
This upsets me,
but it's also positive.

398
00:35:23,660 --> 00:35:25,616
America's rough on the meek.

399
00:35:25,860 --> 00:35:27,816
But they'll inherit the earth.

400
00:35:28,060 --> 00:35:30,858
- What?
- They'll inherit the earth.

401
00:35:34,380 --> 00:35:36,257
That's bullshit.

402
00:35:36,900 --> 00:35:38,856
I heard it on TV.

403
00:35:39,340 --> 00:35:42,696
The meek may inherit
money from relatives,

404
00:35:42,940 --> 00:35:44,612
but not the earth.

405
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:48,132
The only good thing about the meek
is they make...

406
00:35:49,460 --> 00:35:52,213
life easier for those who have moxie.

407
00:35:53,460 --> 00:35:55,416
Can you learn to have it?

408
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:03,013
You either have it or you don't.

409
00:36:14,260 --> 00:36:15,454
Stop!

410
00:36:20,260 --> 00:36:23,377
Hey Charlie,
you've kept him in good shape.

411
00:36:23,860 --> 00:36:26,420
We've been riding him all day.

412
00:36:29,860 --> 00:36:31,134
Get off.

413
00:36:32,020 --> 00:36:35,251
- What?
- Get off my horse.

414
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:38,140
Am I speaking Arabic, get off!

415
00:36:41,420 --> 00:36:43,456
You're scaring my girlfriend.

416
00:36:43,700 --> 00:36:47,613
This is my property,
that's my horse,

417
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:52,378
if I decide to shoot you
the law is on my side.

418
00:36:52,620 --> 00:36:55,930
- Not so sure about that.
- Get off.

419
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:59,855
Relax, it's a misunderstanding
but we'll resolve it.

420
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:04,252
I don't know
what your friend's thinking

421
00:37:04,500 --> 00:37:07,173
but you'd better tell him to get off!

422
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:08,455
Get down.

423
00:37:10,740 --> 00:37:12,093
All right.

424
00:37:15,580 --> 00:37:17,252
Not for you or your rifle,

425
00:37:18,220 --> 00:37:21,417
but 'cause my girl asked me,
and I'd do anything for her.

426
00:37:21,660 --> 00:37:24,015
Unlike you Charlie, I have priorities.

427
00:37:24,260 --> 00:37:27,377
I don't give a damn
about your priorities.

428
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:30,180
And quit calling me Charlie.

429
00:37:39,620 --> 00:37:41,292
I'm rather disappointed,

430
00:37:41,540 --> 00:37:44,498
after all our chats, now you embarrass
me in front of my girl?

431
00:37:44,740 --> 00:37:48,699
I should kick your ass just for that.
Let's go baby.

432
00:37:48,940 --> 00:37:52,376
- You're not going anywhere.
- Put the rifle down!

433
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:56,209
- Put it down.
- They're the thieves.

434
00:37:56,460 --> 00:37:59,179
Thanks, officer.
Charlie, are you insane?

435
00:37:59,420 --> 00:38:02,651
- Pointing a gun at your friends?
- Calm down.

436
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:07,018
Both of you calm down.
What happened?

437
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:09,376
- He stole my horse.
- Not true.

438
00:38:09,620 --> 00:38:11,258
The horse is here!

439
00:38:11,500 --> 00:38:14,253
They came on my property,
stole my horse

440
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:16,411
and that guy threatened me.

441
00:38:16,660 --> 00:38:17,888
What?

442
00:38:18,140 --> 00:38:20,893
- Don't you start!
- Calm down.

443
00:38:21,140 --> 00:38:23,210
- Where's the horse?
- There.

444
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:26,816
The white one,
they took it without asking.

445
00:38:27,060 --> 00:38:28,618
- From my property.
- Wait!

446
00:38:28,860 --> 00:38:32,819
Charlie always lets me use the horses
so long as I bring this.

447
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:35,176
He wasn't here so we took the horse,

448
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:37,376
came back then he attacked me.

449
00:38:37,620 --> 00:38:39,338
You think this is the Far West?

450
00:38:39,580 --> 00:38:42,014
- This is the valley.
- You're holding the rifle!

451
00:38:42,260 --> 00:38:43,898
I don't even know him.

452
00:38:44,140 --> 00:38:45,732
He takes medication,

453
00:38:45,980 --> 00:38:48,255
this is what happens if he forgets to.

454
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:52,254
- Liar!
- You should take your medication.

455
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:55,651
- My name isn't Charlie!
- Put them in the car.

456
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:03,211
Do you really know Charlie?

457
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:05,896
Sure, why do you ask?

458
00:39:07,380 --> 00:39:10,338
You can tell me if you don't,
it's all right.

459
00:39:12,460 --> 00:39:15,816
He keeps insisting
his name isn't Charlie.

460
00:39:16,060 --> 00:39:20,019
So? I don't know
if he has a different name,

461
00:39:20,260 --> 00:39:22,216
I've always called him Charlie.

462
00:39:26,460 --> 00:39:28,052
You mad at me?

463
00:39:31,420 --> 00:39:32,773
Shit!

464
00:39:33,260 --> 00:39:34,659
Great.

465
00:39:47,580 --> 00:39:49,332
I take better care of my animals

466
00:39:49,580 --> 00:39:52,014
than you take care of your children.

467
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:53,534
Right.

468
00:39:53,780 --> 00:39:56,340
Tell me exactly what happened.

469
00:40:02,740 --> 00:40:04,890
Sir, I just want to say that...

470
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:08,216
I know you're upset but...

471
00:40:09,260 --> 00:40:11,774
Tobe had nothing to do with it.

472
00:40:12,860 --> 00:40:16,250
I take full responsibility
for what happened.

473
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:18,536
You don't need to apologize.

474
00:40:18,780 --> 00:40:23,808
I think it's important to take
responsibility for our own actions.

475
00:40:24,260 --> 00:40:27,218
Nothing's more important
than taking responsibility...

476
00:40:27,460 --> 00:40:30,213
Not even
involving a minor in a crime?

477
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:33,613
Okay...

478
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:39,817
But this isn't the case
'cause I didn't break the law.

479
00:40:40,580 --> 00:40:42,616
It was a misunderstanding.

480
00:40:44,780 --> 00:40:46,930
Tobe, tell your friend here...

481
00:40:47,860 --> 00:40:51,136
he needs to be more honest
to gain my trust.

482
00:40:51,380 --> 00:40:54,213
- I don't care if he has your trust!
- Hey!

483
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:16,975
See you, Lonnie.
Thanks.

484
00:41:52,220 --> 00:41:53,778
- Stop!
- Let go!

485
00:41:54,020 --> 00:41:56,056
You sit down and talk to me!

486
00:41:56,300 --> 00:41:58,609
I don't want to talk to you.

487
00:41:59,180 --> 00:42:01,171
- Let go!
- Stop!

488
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:03,694
Fuck you!

489
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:07,491
Don't say that to me, I'm your father.
Understand?

490
00:42:12,700 --> 00:42:14,292
I'm her fucking father.

491
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:19,091
If I see you with that psychopath,
I'll kick your ass!

492
00:42:32,620 --> 00:42:34,417
Wait, go back in.

493
00:42:34,660 --> 00:42:36,890
- Stop it, dammit!
- Let go!

494
00:42:37,140 --> 00:42:39,096
Go back in, what are...

495
00:42:45,740 --> 00:42:47,856
Sorry.

496
00:42:48,260 --> 00:42:51,138
- Please, leave me alone.
- You okay?

497
00:42:51,380 --> 00:42:53,735
Get the fuck away!

498
00:43:18,780 --> 00:43:22,136
- What are you doing?
- Knocking on your window.

499
00:43:22,380 --> 00:43:24,610
- What were you doing?
- Sleeping.

500
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:28,574
What happened to the window?

501
00:43:29,780 --> 00:43:32,135
It was an accident.

502
00:43:32,860 --> 00:43:35,579
- He didn't hit you, did he?
- No.

503
00:43:35,820 --> 00:43:37,970
- You swear?
- Yes.

504
00:43:38,260 --> 00:43:40,091
What did he say about me?

505
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:47,812
He just said he never wants me
to see you again.

506
00:43:53,060 --> 00:43:57,611
- Do you plan on obeying him?
- No way.

507
00:44:02,260 --> 00:44:04,535
Wanna take a walk?

508
00:44:04,780 --> 00:44:06,372
I can't.

509
00:44:06,620 --> 00:44:09,293
There's a religious parade tonight.

510
00:44:09,540 --> 00:44:13,499
Spanish Lutherans,
never seen such enthusiasm.

511
00:44:13,780 --> 00:44:15,930
I can't, not tonight.

512
00:44:16,460 --> 00:44:18,894
- How about tomorrow?
- I'll be away.

513
00:44:19,540 --> 00:44:23,499
I'm going to San Diego for the weekend
with April and her folks.

514
00:44:23,820 --> 00:44:26,937
- Can I see you Monday morning?
- Yes, but not here.

515
00:44:27,180 --> 00:44:29,455
'Cause of my dad...

516
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:32,692
- I'll come to your place.
- Okay, when?

517
00:44:33,580 --> 00:44:35,571
How about 10:02.

518
00:44:36,860 --> 00:44:41,092
- Why so late?
- How about 10:01?

519
00:44:42,460 --> 00:44:44,212
That's better.

520
00:44:46,100 --> 00:44:48,011
Crazy cowboy!

521
00:44:50,580 --> 00:44:52,172
You love me?

522
00:44:53,820 --> 00:44:56,380
Yes, now go!

523
00:45:03,580 --> 00:45:05,138
Bye.

524
00:45:27,140 --> 00:45:28,573
Dear Joe,

525
00:45:28,820 --> 00:45:33,575
sorry it's been so long
since I've been in touch.

526
00:45:33,820 --> 00:45:37,608
You thought this cowboy
had galloped into the afterlife?

527
00:45:37,860 --> 00:45:39,816
Hope you haven't forgotten me.

528
00:45:44,300 --> 00:45:46,131
I've been meaning to write,

529
00:45:46,380 --> 00:45:48,211
but was busy working

530
00:45:48,460 --> 00:45:51,816
and trying to have fun
in my free time.

531
00:45:55,340 --> 00:45:58,776
I know you worry
about me being lonely

532
00:45:59,020 --> 00:46:02,137
but you'll be glad to know
I found a super gal,

533
00:46:02,380 --> 00:46:03,859
her name is October.

534
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:07,490
There are 8 million people here,
but she's the one for me.

535
00:46:07,740 --> 00:46:10,698
She introduced me to her folks,
I'm like part of the family,

536
00:46:10,940 --> 00:46:13,249
we're inseparable now.

537
00:46:35,860 --> 00:46:38,010
Hey, it's me, Twig.

538
