01:11:27,980 --> 01:11:29,652
What?

800
01:11:30,540 --> 01:11:34,135
I told you I'd figure something out,
look...

801
01:11:34,380 --> 01:11:36,769
It took time but I got some money,

802
01:11:37,020 --> 01:11:40,137
we'll live of off it,
we can settle down...

803
01:11:40,380 --> 01:11:44,214
take Lonnie in,
or do anything you want.

804
01:11:44,460 --> 01:11:46,212
I put some things in it.

805
01:11:46,460 --> 01:11:49,975
Didn't know what to get, I was so
excited I got 7 of everything.

806
01:11:50,620 --> 01:11:52,451
I didn't find 7 bras though.

807
01:11:52,700 --> 01:11:54,656
But I did get your dress.

808
01:11:54,900 --> 01:11:59,052
I'm sure you'll need other stuff
that I don't know about.

809
01:12:00,340 --> 01:12:02,900
Honey, why that face?

810
01:12:03,300 --> 01:12:06,451
My dad will be here soon,
you'd better go.

811
01:12:06,700 --> 01:12:08,531
Wait, there's time...

812
01:12:08,780 --> 01:12:11,135
Grab your things, this is our chance.

813
01:12:11,380 --> 01:12:14,895
- Put away the suitcase, please.
- Wait, why?

814
01:12:15,140 --> 01:12:18,894
- My dad will kill me if he sees it.
- Wait, stop!

815
01:12:19,140 --> 01:12:21,700
Relax, we'll be far away
once he notices.

816
01:12:21,940 --> 01:12:25,694
I already told you
I don't want to leave!

817
01:12:30,020 --> 01:12:33,137
That wasn't you talking, I know.

818
01:12:33,380 --> 01:12:36,338
- Then who was it?
- The voice of someone else.

819
01:12:36,580 --> 01:12:38,332
It was your fear talking.

820
01:12:38,580 --> 01:12:40,969
I don't know what you mean,
but you should go.

821
01:12:41,220 --> 01:12:43,176
October, listen! Honey...

822
01:12:43,700 --> 01:12:46,373
I know you're afraid
but this is our chance.

823
01:12:46,620 --> 01:12:49,771
Look inside yourself
and listen to your heart's voice.

824
01:12:50,020 --> 01:12:53,217
This is my heart, this is my voice,
I want you to go!

825
01:12:53,460 --> 01:12:56,213
- Don't shout!
- Well you're not listening to me!

826
01:12:56,460 --> 01:12:59,133
I said you have to go,
what's with you?

827
01:12:59,380 --> 01:13:01,132
What's with you!

828
01:13:25,380 --> 01:13:26,733
Sweetness...

829
01:13:28,660 --> 01:13:30,332
Sweetness, I didn't...

830
01:13:32,380 --> 01:13:34,132
Do you hear me, honey?

831
01:13:34,860 --> 01:13:36,612
Can you hear me?

832
01:13:38,260 --> 01:13:40,012
Keep breathing.

833
01:13:40,260 --> 01:13:42,012
Please keep breathing.

834
01:13:45,940 --> 01:13:47,293
Breathe.

835
01:13:56,260 --> 01:13:58,091
911, can I help you?

836
01:13:58,340 --> 01:14:00,490
Hello? 911 here, hello?

837
01:14:26,220 --> 01:14:27,972
You home?

838
01:14:29,780 --> 01:14:31,133
Tobe?

839
01:14:32,060 --> 01:14:33,413
Lonnie?

840
01:15:00,860 --> 01:15:02,771
Somebody help my daughter!

841
01:15:03,140 --> 01:15:05,495
Somebody help my daughter!

842
01:16:15,300 --> 01:16:19,578
- Do you own other guns?
- Yes, but they're locked up.

843
01:16:19,820 --> 01:16:21,333
Was that one?

844
01:16:22,380 --> 01:16:24,735
He managed to get at it.

845
01:16:24,980 --> 01:16:26,891
But the lock wasn't broken.

846
01:16:27,140 --> 01:16:29,779
Listen, he managed in some way!

847
01:16:30,460 --> 01:16:32,610
Did she say anything?

848
01:16:33,060 --> 01:16:34,209
No.

849
01:16:35,660 --> 01:16:37,218
She'd already...

850
01:16:37,460 --> 01:16:39,416
Iost consciousness.

851
01:16:39,700 --> 01:16:41,850
- And your son?
- No.

852
01:16:42,220 --> 01:16:44,131
He wasn't there.

853
01:16:44,380 --> 01:16:47,690
- Does he have access to the guns?
- No way!

854
01:16:48,660 --> 01:16:52,255
- His prints were on the gun.
- What!

855
01:16:52,620 --> 01:16:56,374
- Maybe it was an accident.
- No, it wasn't!

856
01:16:56,620 --> 01:16:58,178
It was...

857
01:16:59,220 --> 01:17:03,577
Nobody's ever seen
that cowboy you mentioned.

858
01:17:20,980 --> 01:17:22,493
Hey, Twig!

859
01:17:28,420 --> 01:17:29,455
Hi.

860
01:17:37,860 --> 01:17:40,215
Tobe got shot.

861
01:17:40,660 --> 01:17:42,412
Yeah, I know.

862
01:17:43,860 --> 01:17:46,294
- I'm wounded too.
- Who did it?

863
01:17:47,140 --> 01:17:49,096
She didn't say anything to anybody?

864
01:17:49,340 --> 01:17:51,092
She's in a coma.

865
01:17:55,660 --> 01:17:57,935
It was Wade.

866
01:17:58,180 --> 01:18:00,535
- Really?
- Yes.

867
01:18:01,220 --> 01:18:02,972
I came to say hello.

868
01:18:03,220 --> 01:18:06,974
I'd decided to leave,
to go away for a while.

869
01:18:07,740 --> 01:18:09,890
She wanted to come with me.

870
01:18:11,300 --> 01:18:14,576
We were talking
and didn't hear him come home.

871
01:18:14,820 --> 01:18:19,018
He shot at me but Tobe
got in the way so it hit her.

872
01:18:19,260 --> 01:18:22,218
She was trying to protect me
and got hit!

873
01:18:24,220 --> 01:18:27,371
How could something like that happen?

874
01:18:27,620 --> 01:18:30,373
He shot at me too but I ran away.

875
01:18:30,620 --> 01:18:32,576
Where did it hit you?

876
01:18:35,860 --> 01:18:39,773
- Does it hurt?
- No, it's just a scratch.

877
01:18:40,740 --> 01:18:42,492
I'll be fine.

878
01:18:42,860 --> 01:18:45,613
My fingerprints were on the gun.

879
01:18:46,460 --> 01:18:49,611
I have to talk
to the Police tomorrow.

880
01:18:55,660 --> 01:18:57,173
Twig...

881
01:18:57,540 --> 01:18:59,496
I want you to listen to me.

882
01:19:00,660 --> 01:19:05,017
It's best if you grab your things
and leave with me now.

883
01:19:05,260 --> 01:19:07,490
- I can't.
- Sure you can.

884
01:19:08,260 --> 01:19:10,216
Sooner or later

885
01:19:10,580 --> 01:19:14,334
the Police will figure out
that your dad did it.

886
01:19:14,580 --> 01:19:17,333
When that happens, they'll arrest him.

887
01:19:18,420 --> 01:19:22,095
Then they'll stick you
in a foster home.

888
01:19:22,340 --> 01:19:24,570
- No they won't.
- They will.

889
01:19:25,660 --> 01:19:27,571
It's the truth.

890
01:19:28,700 --> 01:19:31,009
You'll end up in a state orphanage,

891
01:19:32,260 --> 01:19:34,012
do you understand?

892
01:19:36,620 --> 01:19:39,771
It's the worst thing
that could happen to a kid.

893
01:19:40,020 --> 01:19:42,170
I don't want that to happen to you.

894
01:19:43,060 --> 01:19:45,813
If you want,
I'll take you out of here.

895
01:19:46,060 --> 01:19:47,573
We'll hide out for a while.

896
01:19:48,460 --> 01:19:52,135
When Tobe's better
we'll come back to get her.

897
01:19:55,660 --> 01:19:57,616
What do you say, pal?

898
01:19:58,420 --> 01:20:00,411
Wanna come with me?

899
01:20:01,780 --> 01:20:03,099
Yes.

900
01:20:03,660 --> 01:20:05,013
All right.

901
01:20:06,020 --> 01:20:09,376
Then pack a bag
and grab me a blanket,

902
01:20:09,620 --> 01:20:12,088
we'll meet in the alley out back, go.

903
01:21:01,380 --> 01:21:03,132
C'mon champ.

904
01:21:21,460 --> 01:21:24,418
Mr. Sommers, she woke up!

905
01:21:32,860 --> 01:21:34,179
Hi.

906
01:21:41,340 --> 01:21:42,659
Hi.

907
01:21:47,620 --> 01:21:49,451
What happened?

908
01:21:52,260 --> 01:21:54,091
You were unconscious.

909
01:21:54,340 --> 01:21:55,693
I feel...

910
01:21:55,940 --> 01:21:57,896
so strange.

911
01:22:06,860 --> 01:22:08,816
Where's Lonnie?

912
01:22:47,500 --> 01:22:50,651
This is the highest point
there is around here.

913
01:22:54,860 --> 01:22:56,816
Are you crying, buddy?

914
01:22:57,860 --> 01:22:59,418
Sorry.

915
01:23:03,060 --> 01:23:07,099
Don't say sorry for crying,
it's nothing to be ashamed of.

916
01:23:12,780 --> 01:23:14,691
The only time I don't cry

917
01:23:15,060 --> 01:23:18,211
is in front
of people I consider enemies.

918
01:23:27,220 --> 01:23:29,051
Will Tobe get better?

919
01:23:32,220 --> 01:23:34,370
Is that what you're worried about?

920
01:23:41,460 --> 01:23:43,815
Yes, she sure will get better.

921
01:23:47,460 --> 01:23:50,611
- Did you find him?
- He's not here.

922
01:24:21,020 --> 01:24:23,170
A guy saw him in Santa Clarita.

923
01:24:25,820 --> 01:24:29,176
His real name is Martin Lassen,
he's from Receda.

924
01:24:29,420 --> 01:24:32,378
He spent a year in jail for robbery.

925
01:24:36,020 --> 01:24:37,772
We almost there?

926
01:24:38,620 --> 01:24:39,735
Almost.

927
01:25:05,980 --> 01:25:07,333
Come here,

928
01:25:07,620 --> 01:25:09,770
let me show you something.

929
01:25:10,420 --> 01:25:11,853
What?

930
01:25:13,660 --> 01:25:15,810
C'mon, trust me!

931
01:25:19,700 --> 01:25:21,099
Let's go.

932
01:25:44,260 --> 01:25:46,216
You hold it for a bit.

933
01:25:53,100 --> 01:25:54,613
Where are you going?

934
01:25:55,220 --> 01:25:56,573
Relax!

935
01:25:57,460 --> 01:25:59,416
I'm not going anywhere.

936
01:26:05,980 --> 01:26:07,493
Where are you?

937
01:26:07,820 --> 01:26:09,572
Here with you.

938
01:26:10,220 --> 01:26:12,688
Now try to find your way back.

939
01:26:38,060 --> 01:26:42,212
- What was that?
- An animal that's scared like us.

940
01:26:54,820 --> 01:26:56,378
Don't run.

941
01:26:57,460 --> 01:27:00,418
Move, but not as if you're afraid.

942
01:27:01,060 --> 01:27:04,177
Move like a panther, with courage

943
01:27:04,420 --> 01:27:06,172
and you'll be fine.

944
01:27:11,460 --> 01:27:14,213
- Lonnie!
- Relax!

945
01:27:21,380 --> 01:27:22,813
Down there.

946
01:27:26,100 --> 01:27:28,455
- There he is!
- Stop!

947
01:27:35,260 --> 01:27:37,569
C'mon, hop on Lonnie.

948
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:42,058
Don't shoot!

949
01:28:09,860 --> 01:28:13,409
They'll never find us,
I don't even know where we are.

950
01:29:03,260 --> 01:29:05,012
Where are we?

951
01:29:38,900 --> 01:29:42,176
The horse doesn't like
how I treated him, he's right.

952
01:29:42,420 --> 01:29:44,172
No, he's fine.

953
01:29:53,420 --> 01:29:54,773
Darn.

954
01:30:00,220 --> 01:30:03,132
This isn't exactly how I pictured it.

955
01:30:03,620 --> 01:30:05,531
I'm really sorry.

956
01:30:05,780 --> 01:30:07,691
Don't worry.

957
01:30:08,820 --> 01:30:11,778
When real cowboys used to live here,

958
01:30:12,620 --> 01:30:15,373
they called each other "partner",
it was right.

959
01:30:15,780 --> 01:30:18,340
They were used to sharing everything.

960
01:30:30,660 --> 01:30:32,412
Know what?

961
01:30:42,660 --> 01:30:44,616
We need to get some sleep.

962
01:32:49,020 --> 01:32:52,569
- Music cheers people up.
- Yes, ma'am.

963
01:32:52,820 --> 01:32:56,176
- Don't you agree?
- Yes, a city...

964
01:32:56,420 --> 01:32:58,456
isn't a city without dancing.

965
01:32:58,700 --> 01:33:00,850
Would you care to dance?

966
01:33:03,460 --> 01:33:07,851
I don't reckon I'm worthy
to dance with a lady like you.

967
01:33:08,980 --> 01:33:10,732
But I asked you!

968
01:33:12,660 --> 01:33:15,333
- All right.
- Good, let's dance.

969
01:33:15,580 --> 01:33:17,536
Be right there.

970
01:33:18,060 --> 01:33:20,972
- I believe this is yours.
- Thanks.

971
01:33:24,060 --> 01:33:27,496
Time for our new sheriff
and his lady

972
01:33:27,740 --> 01:33:29,332
to dance!

973
01:33:30,620 --> 01:33:33,771
- Duty calls, see you around.
- Sure thing.

974
01:34:53,820 --> 01:34:55,890
- Stop!
- Take it easy.

975
01:34:56,580 --> 01:34:58,332
You take it easy.

976
01:34:58,900 --> 01:35:01,175
Twig, come here and bring Lightning.

977
01:35:01,420 --> 01:35:02,819
Lonnie, step away.

978
01:35:06,180 --> 01:35:09,855
Wade, take one step near him
and I'll shoot you.

979
01:35:10,220 --> 01:35:12,336
Hold on, nobody hurts anybody.

980
01:35:12,580 --> 01:35:17,210
- Let's put the guns down and talk.
- Put your gun down, now!

981
01:35:17,460 --> 01:35:20,213
Easy, with one finger, slowly.

982
01:35:22,780 --> 01:35:25,692
You too, take off your belt.

983
01:35:26,140 --> 01:35:27,653
Take it off!

984
01:35:34,260 --> 01:35:35,659
Untie the horse.

985
01:35:36,620 --> 01:35:39,692
- He shot Tobe!
- Shut your damn mouth!

986
01:35:39,940 --> 01:35:41,293
The girl's not dead.

987
01:35:41,540 --> 01:35:44,850
Lie all you want,
but we know you shot her.

988
01:35:45,100 --> 01:35:47,773
- You're crazy!
- Even Lonnie knows!

989
01:35:48,020 --> 01:35:50,739
- Nutcase, you lied to my son!
- Harlan!

990
01:36:08,620 --> 01:36:10,815
Come on Lonnie!

991
01:36:15,260 --> 01:36:16,613
Let's go.

992
01:36:39,220 --> 01:36:40,573
Damn!

993
01:36:48,260 --> 01:36:51,377
- You okay?
- Yes, hold this here...

994
01:36:51,620 --> 01:36:53,099
and press hard.

995
01:36:53,700 --> 01:36:55,531
C'mon, keep pressing.

996
01:36:55,780 --> 01:36:57,736
We have to get out of here.

997
01:37:45,540 --> 01:37:48,896
We've gotta move, help me get up.

998
01:37:50,900 --> 01:37:52,333
And Lightning?

999
01:37:52,780 --> 01:37:54,133
Go!

1000
01:38:12,900 --> 01:38:14,413
Stay down.

1001
01:38:19,980 --> 01:38:21,459
Will you be okay?

1002
01:38:21,700 --> 01:38:23,099
Hope so.

1003
01:38:23,340 --> 01:38:25,490
Don't wanna die in a place like this.

1004
01:38:26,580 --> 01:38:28,332
I don't like it one bit.

1005
01:38:40,980 --> 01:38:42,333
Listen,

1006
01:38:42,700 --> 01:38:45,817
stand up and see who's outside.

1007
01:38:49,660 --> 01:38:51,935
- It's Lightning.
- What's he doing?

1008
01:38:52,180 --> 01:38:55,217
- Nothing, just standing there.
- He'll give us away.

1009
01:38:56,300 --> 01:38:59,736
Bring him around back,
put him in the garage.

1010
01:38:59,980 --> 01:39:01,857
Wait, look at me.

1011
01:39:02,220 --> 01:39:04,529
You can do it, go!

1012
01:39:05,060 --> 01:39:07,016
Go, you can do it!

1013
01:39:44,620 --> 01:39:47,976
He was spooked, but he's fine now.

1014
01:40:31,460 --> 01:40:32,495
Stop!

1015
01:40:37,180 --> 01:40:38,738
Don't!

1016
01:40:57,260 --> 01:40:58,932
Stay here.

1017
01:41:03,940 --> 01:41:05,896
Listen, he shot your sister.

1018
01:41:06,500 --> 01:41:08,775
Lonnie, he's the one who shot Tobe.

1019
01:41:09,020 --> 01:41:12,296
- That's not true!
- She'll tell you herself.

1020
01:41:12,540 --> 01:41:14,292
She'll tell you.

1021
01:42:36,860 --> 01:42:38,612
What should we say?

1022
01:42:52,460 --> 01:42:54,291
Nothing,

1023
01:42:57,700 --> 01:42:59,452
just pray for him.

